132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 990
S.P. 424 In Senate, March 11, 2025
Resolve, Requiring the Office of the Attorney General to Develop
and Promote an Optional Online Registry Informing Landlords of
Their Rights and Obligations
Reference to the Committee on Judiciary suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator CURRY of Waldo.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Office of the Attorney General online landlord registry. Resolved:
2 That the Office of the Attorney General shall develop and promote an optional online
3 landlord registry for landlords renting rooms within their primary residences. The registry
4 must include information informing landlords of their rights and obligations as landlords.
5 SUMMARY
66 This resolve directs the Office of the Attorney General to develop and promote an
77 optional online landlord registry for landlords renting rooms within their primary
88 residences. It stipulates that the registry must include information informing landlords of
99 their rights and obligations as landlords.
